#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""dt_find — voice/text vinyl record finder powered by an LLM.

Describe a record in plain English — vague, informal, partial — and the LLM
searches Discogs on your behalf, opens the release page for confirmation,
then optionally prints a sleeve label.

Usage
-----
    ./dt_find                              # voice input (default)
    ./dt_find --text                       # force typed description
    ./dt_find "the blue Miles Davis one"   # description inline
    ./dt_find --backend anthropic          # use Claude Haiku via API
    ./dt_find --backend local              # use local OpenAI-compatible LLM

Saved settings  (~/.discogstool/find_config)
--------------------------------------------
    backend=anthropic                          # or: local  (default: local)
    llm_url=http://wintermute.local:8000/v1    # for backend=local
    llm_model=mlx-community/Qwen3.5-122B-A10B-4bit
    find_anthropic_model=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001  # optional model override

For backend=anthropic the API key is read from ~/.discogstool/beatport_auth.json
("anthropic_api_key") or the ANTHROPIC_API_KEY environment variable.

Voice dependencies (installed separately, see requirements.txt):
    pip install sounddevice SpeechRecognition
"""

